    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.28" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">28</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">CHARLIE CHAPLIN FILM COMPANY
                        <lb/>
                    1416 LA BREA AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    LOS ANGELES, CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 7,24</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear John:</salute>
                </opener> 
                <p>Am mighty gald<sic>glad</sic> to hear the news regarding the possible sales. I wrote Rupert Hughes and mentioned it in my le<del/><add>t</add>ter, saying that Samuel <hi rend="caps">J</hi>,s<sic><hi rend="caps">J</hi>'s</sic> words about Goldsmith could be reversed to "<del>w</del><add>W</add>as ever poet so fortunate before." I feel that your writings will eventually go in pictures and that they would be far more worth <del>whi</del> while than much of the p<unclear>a</unclear>ffle now being screened. Some writers only sell for a period of five years--that would give you a chance to resell and have the pictures made better--for instance, Rex Beach has had The Spoilers made twice. It may be worth remembering--but your agents know that no doubt.</p>
                
                <p>I sent Mr.Long a paragraph or so about your work at the Ebell Club. Have had no further word from him but suppose he got it. There is an article in Classic which I have not seen--the September issue--a picture of you,<hi rend="caps">R.H.</hi>and myself may be in it, as I sent one.</p>
                
                <p>I'd love to come there for a time..but I hardly know how I can get that far ahead of the wolf.</p>
                
                <p>Did I tell you that I was leading Boni's list--and my name is also on the <del>b</del><add>p</add>ack pages amongst names I used to love and dream about as a boy. I may wake up yet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Best always John.</salute>
                
                    <signed>Jim Tully</signed>
                    <signed>Jim Tully</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>I sent the Review article in..I don't know how good it is..I hope they like it..for your sake..</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
